  "prompt": "What are div1 and div2 on topcoder?",
  "response": "On Topcoder, \"Div 1\" and \"Div 2\" refer to the two divisions used in competitive programming contests, specifically in Single Round Matches (SRMs). \n\n- **Div 1**: This division is generally for more experienced or higher-rated competitors. Typically, participants in Div 1 have a rating above a certain threshold (usually set around 1200 or higher). The problems in this division tend to be more challenging.\n\n- **Div 2**: This division is designed for less experienced competitors or those with lower ratings. Participants in Div 2 have a rating below the threshold that qualifies them for Div 1. The problems in this division are generally easier compared to those in Div 1.\n\nThe division structure allows participants to compete against others of similar skill levels, which can help foster a more balanced and enjoyable competitive experience. Ratings are updated after each contest, and participants can move between divisions based on their performance.",
